<div id="review_444694454" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/444694454" />
    <a title="Anna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2682377-anna"><img alt="Anna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1255196133p2/2682377.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/444694454?book_show_action=true">Oct 30, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anna" href="/user/show/2682377-anna">Anna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2682377-anna?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2682377-anna?shelf=sci-fi-fantasy">sci-fi-fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer444694454" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1216703969082293645"> I had the pleasure of meeting Chris Howard in Denver at a trade show and hearing him talk about his book. I immediately knew that I had to read it for a couple of reasons. As a bookseller, I am constantly on the lookout for books that will appeal to young men, because they seem to be harder to keep interested in reading, if I may briefly overgeneralize. Also, this one sounded really awesome. I was not disappointed.<br/><br/> Rootless takes place in the future, when locusts have destroyed all animals but </span>
  <span id="freeText1216703969082293645" style="display:none"> I had the pleasure of meeting Chris Howard in Denver at a trade show and hearing him talk about his book. I immediately knew that I had to read it for a couple of reasons. As a bookseller, I am constantly on the lookout for books that will appeal to young men, because they seem to be harder to keep interested in reading, if I may briefly overgeneralize. Also, this one sounded really awesome. I was not disappointed.<br /><br /> Rootless takes place in the future, when locusts have destroyed all animals but humans(althought they'll eat them too, given the chance) and all plants but a genetically-altered corn. Banyan and his father have spent their whole lives building trees out of scrap metal and the like, but Banyan's father was recently taken. Banyan finds an unexpected link to his dad at a house he's building a forest for, and his life takes a lot of turns from there. This book is gritty and incredibly fast-paced. It's great for fans of Hunger Games or Pure by Julianna Baggott. There's a male main character, lots of action and violence, and not so much of that whiny teenage angst. I loved it.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1216703969082293645" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


