  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/649264155" />
    <a title="Rusty&#39;s Ghost Engine (also known as.......... Jinky Spring)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21530568-rusty-s-ghost-engine-also-known-as-jinky-spring"><img alt="Rusty&#39;s Ghost Engine (also known as.......... Jinky Spring)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1459806787p2/21530568.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/649264155?book_show_action=true">Jun 23, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rusty&#39;s Ghost Engine (also known as.......... Jinky Spring)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rusty&#39;s Ghost Engine (also known as.......... Jinky Spring)" href="/user/show/21530568-rusty-s-ghost-engine-also-known-as-jinky-spring">Rusty&#39;s Ghost Engine (also known as.......... Jinky Spring)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21530568-rusty-s-ghost-engine-also-known-as-jinky-spring?shelf=potential-to-go-big">potential-to-go-big</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21530568-rusty-s-ghost-engine-also-known-as-jinky-spring?shelf=sci-fi-or-dystopia">sci-fi-or-dystopia</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21530568-rusty-s-ghost-engine-also-known-as-jinky-spring?shelf=that-don-t-impress-me-much">that-don-t-impress-me-much</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21530568-rusty-s-ghost-engine-also-known-as-jinky-spring?shelf=series-lost-interest">series-lost-interest</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer649264155" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11446396828138195379">What a bloody train wreck...<br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380426519ra/852340.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/>Caution! Spoilers once again!<br/>Let me first say I had read the <a href='https://www.goodreads.com' rel='nofollow noopener'>Exodus</a> series before reading this, so maybe that was my mistake as I have higher expectations after reading something good. Usually, books and movies involving the destruction of the planet because of human activity make me feel touched and inspired. I had those powerful emotions when reading Exodus, but I felt NOTHING when I read Rootless. <br/><br/>The story just wasn&apos;t powerful and Banyan (which is a tropical tree </span>
  <span id="freeText11446396828138195379" style="display:none">What a bloody train wreck...<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380426519ra/852340.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>Caution! Spoilers once again!<br>Let me first say I had read the <a href="https://www.goodreads.com" rel="nofollow noopener">Exodus</a> series before reading this, so maybe that was my mistake as I have higher expectations after reading something good. Usually, books and movies involving the destruction of the planet because of human activity make me feel touched and inspired. I had those powerful emotions when reading Exodus, but I felt NOTHING when I read Rootless. <br><br>The story just wasn't powerful and Banyan (which is a tropical tree by the way, I wonder if he'll ever realize that later on?) just didn't seem to be hero material. There wasn't anything special about him other than his father disappearing and being turned into some sort of super tree, but he still had his human features(I didn't intend that to sound rude!). <br><br>I did think the idea of merging the DNA of humans with that of trees to make a much tougher race of trees was quite amazing. But at the end I couldn't understand how Banyan's mother and Zee changed sides from GenTech to that of the escapees so quickly. <br><br>So overall I think this was a poor attempt for an environmental epic and I would much prefer the Exodus series. This novel for me started with promise of something big, but it literally just crashed and burned into a pathetic wreck.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11446396828138195379" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


