<div id="review_519215456" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/519215456" />
    <a title="Jen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4379527-jen"><img alt="Jen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1433611174p2/4379527.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/519215456?book_show_action=true">Jan 27, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jen" href="/user/show/4379527-jen">Jen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4379527-jen?shelf=ya">ya</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4379527-jen?shelf=dystopia">dystopia</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4379527-jen?shelf=science-fiction">science-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4379527-jen?shelf=guy-reads">guy-reads</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer519215456" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11487895092565424904">Rootless is a thought provoking, unusual dystopian story about a future world where some cataclysmic event has caused most living things, with the exception of humans and some really scary locusts, to die. These locusts are so desperate, they have morphed into scary bugs with razor sharp teeth that will eat an entire human being. Very scary. Oh, and a big tech company has control over the one food source available, corn, which is genetically modified to be incredibly nutritious. And because of t</span>
  <span id="freeText11487895092565424904" style="display:none">Rootless is a thought provoking, unusual dystopian story about a future world where some cataclysmic event has caused most living things, with the exception of humans and some really scary locusts, to die. These locusts are so desperate, they have morphed into scary bugs with razor sharp teeth that will eat an entire human being. Very scary. Oh, and a big tech company has control over the one food source available, corn, which is genetically modified to be incredibly nutritious. And because of the lack of trees and forests and such, there are enormous dust storms and the oceans have become scary and take large chunks of the coast on a regular basis. And there is something about the moon being closer to the earth, but I'm not exactly sure why.<br /><br />While I love a good, creepy, depressing dystopian read like anybody else, I felt like there was just a wee bit too much going on to keep track of. I thought it had a lot of promise, and obviously a nice message about trees, and I enjoyed the twisty turns the plot had that kept me on my toes, but ultimately, I just didn't get into the story enough to really enjoy it. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11487895092565424904" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


